attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, Synopsys ARCompact ARC700 cores, version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, stripped

threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The binary is a malicious DDoS bot targeting the RISC-V architecture. It contains strings to craft network packets for an SSDP discovery scan, a technique used in amplification attacks. Key IOCs include the SSDP M-SEARCH template "M-SEARCH * HTTP/1.1\r\nHOST: 255.255.255.255:1900\r\n..." and various HTTP request formats and user-agent strings, suggesting capabilities for launching HTTP floods. The sample is statically linked, typical for malware designed for portability on IoT devices.
